How to use git

1. Use the repository URL located on github.com

2. in the terminal go to the library you want to clone the files to

3. type: git clone <URL>

4. git status to see the changed files

5. git add <filename or *> to add the files to commit list

6. git commit -m "commmitmsg"   it commits changes to the local machine

7. git push    uploads the shit into github.com, auth required.
ngergoo
almafa123

8. to get the files into another machine: go to the repo directory: git pull
